{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, DCN directly connects feature maps from different layers, enabling feature reuse and improving efficiency, which is the main difference between DCN and ResNet.",
    "In the formula representation, the output of a traditional network at the k-th layer is:",
    "For ResNet, an identity function from the preceding layer input is added:",
    "In DCN, all preceding layers are concatenated as input:",
    "x k ¼ H k ½x 0; x 1;::::; x kÀ1 À Á"
  ]
}